        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 6 at 1:20PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 119 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Burleson County. These storms may be producing
locally strong wind gusts and hail. We are monitoring these storms
for the potential of further strengthening.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Caldwell, Somerville, Snook, Lake Somerville State Park &amp; Trailway,
Lyons, Deanville, and Chriesman.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 400 PM CDT for southeastern
Texas.</instruction>
